<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-939-008  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 939 008.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computing Canada  Nov 23 1989 v15 n24 p35(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Plesman Publications Ltd. (Canada) 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Relational Technology launches new image. (renames itself IngresCorp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Campbell, Gordon.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Relational Technology Inc changes its name to Ingres Corp, withits Toronto-based subsidiary now called Ingres Corp Canada.andP;  TheUniversity of Quebec at Montreal has translated the firm's Ingresrelational database management system (DBMS) into Canadian French.andO;Ingres Corp Canada will release the product in early 1990.andP;  IngresDBMS enhancements include compiled database procedures, on-linebackup and international sorting sequences.andP;  Ingres Corp alsoannounces the Intelligent Database product suite which works ontop of the core Ingres DBMS.andP;  Intelligent Database productsinclude Ingres Object Management and Ingres Knowledge Management.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Relational Technology Inc. (names)Ingres Corp. (names)Ingres Corp. Canada (names).andO;Ticker:    RELY.andO;Product:   Ingres (Data base management system) (product development).andO;Topic:     French LanguageImageRelational DBMSForeign LanguagesQuebec, University of (Montreal)CanadaSoftware PublishersLanguage TranslationProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Relational Technology launches new imageandM;TORONTO -- Relational Technology Inc. has changed its name, introduced &quot;thefirst Intelligent Database,&quot; and translated its relational databasemanagement system (RDBMS) to Canadian French.andM;The new name of the company is Ingres Corp., with the Toronto-basedsubsidiary now called Ingres Corp. Canada.andP;  The company's primary product isthe Ingres RDBMS.andM;The University of Quebec at Montreal (UQAM) performed the translation forIngres.andP;  Under the terms of the agreement, UQAM will be able to installIngres on 25 timesharing computers and 50 PC-compatibles.andM;Ingres will maintain and update the software in exchange for maintenance andupdating of the French version by the UQAM Computing Centre.andP;  The centre canalso sell copies of Ingres PC to UQAM students for $100.andM;Joseph Messina, general manager of Ingres Canada, lauded the &quot;technical andsoftware excellence&quot; of the UQAM people.andP;  The French version will beavailable in early 1990.andM;Ingres Intelligent Database improves functions of the core RDBMS, as well asadding two new products, Ingres Object Management and Ingres KnowledgeManagement.andM;The Ingres RDBMS improvements include I/O reduction techniques, compileddatabase procedures, on-line backup, two-phase commit, international sortingsequences and Intelligent Query Optimizer.andM;The two-phase commit protocol maintains data integrity over a distributeddatabase.andP;  The first phase checks that each server has received its part ofan intended update.andP;  The second phase checks that each server hassuccessfully written the data to disk.andP;  Any failure results in a completebackout of the transaction across all servers.andM;The Intelligent Query Optimizer uses the structure of the database, and thestatistical distribution of data in each table, to reduce the amount of dataread from disk for a particular request.andM;The Object Management Extension provides for user-defined data types, as wellas functions and operators which manipulate those data types.andP;  Examples citedby the company include graphics, complex mathematics and CAD (computer-aideddesign) drawings.andM;Ingres Knowledge Management allows an unlimited number of rules to be storedin the database.andP;  Rules can be nested or recursive.andP;  The company claims userscan &quot;program actual business policies into the information managementsystem.&quot;andP;  Knowledge Management also includes a resource control feature, saidto simplify database administration.andM;The Intelligent Database product suite will be available this year on the DECVax platform running under VMS, and in early 1990 on a variety of Unixworkstations.andP;  Messina said versions for Sun Microsystems, Sequent andPyramid systems were scheduled first.andO;</TEXT></DOC>